abstract: The U.S. Senate impeachment trial of President Donald Trump enters its final stage on Wednesday, with senators poised to vote on whether to acquit or convict Trump on charges of abuse of power and obstruction of Congress after laying out their positions in a final flurry of speeches.
snippet: The U.S. Senate impeachment trial of President Donald Trump enters its final stage on Wednesday, with senators poised to vote on whether to acquit or convict Trump on charges of abuse of power and obstruction of Congress after laying out their pos...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The U.S. Senate impeachment trial of President Donald Trump enters its final stage on Wednesday, with senators poised to vote on whether to acquit or convict Trump on charges of abuse of power and obstruction of Congress after laying out their positions in a final flurry of speeches.

abstract: Supporters of President Trump gathered on Wednesday outside the Youth Climate and Clean Energy Town Hall in Concord, N.H.

abstract: The father of a student killed in the 2018 Florida high school massacre apologized Wednesday for disrupting President Donald Trump's State of the Union address by shouting as the president said the rights of gun owners are under siege.
snippet: The father of a student killed in the 2018 Florida high school massacre apologized Wednesday for disrupting President Donald Trump's State of the Union address by shouting as the president said the rights of gun owners are under siege.
lead_paragraph: FORT LAUDERDALE, Fla. — The father of a student killed in the 2018 Florida high school massacre apologized Wednesday for disrupting President Donald Trump's State of the Union address by shouting as the president said the rights of gun owners are under siege.
headline_main: Parkland Dad Apologizes for State of the Union Outburst
headline_print_headline: Parkland Dad Apologizes for State of the Union Outburst

abstract: The British government is questioning the BBC’s public funding and even picking fights with papers that have backed Prime Minister Boris Johnson with gusto.
snippet: The British government is questioning the BBC’s public funding and even picking fights with papers that have backed Prime Minister Boris Johnson with gusto.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — When Prime Minister Boris Johnson delivered a fireside chat last week to mark Britain’s departure from the European Union, he did not ask the BBC to tape it, preferring to use an in-house video crew. The BBC, in turn, refused to air his remarks on that history-making evening.

abstract: Former Secretary of State Rex Tillerson made a call for greater U.S. political and economic involvement in the world, and said he hopes that President Donald Trump will send a message in Tuesday night's State of the Union address that would reassure the country's allies.
snippet: Former Secretary of State Rex Tillerson made a call for greater U.S. political and economic involvement in the world, and said he hopes that President Donald Trump will send a message in Tuesday night's State of the Union address that would reassu...
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Former Secretary of State Rex Tillerson made a call for greater U.S. political and economic involvement in the world, and said he hopes that President Donald Trump will send a message in Tuesday night's State of the Union address that would reassure the country's allies.
headline_main: Former Secretary of State Tillerson Calls for Trump to Reassure U.S. Allies
headline_print_headline: Former Secretary of State Tillerson Calls for Trump to Reassure U.S. Allies

abstract: Comedians have always been tempted to make fun of tragedies, but a new controversy exposes how dark humor has evolved and expanded.
snippet: Comedians have always been tempted to make fun of tragedies, but a new controversy exposes how dark humor has evolved and expanded.
lead_paragraph: On the day of Kobe Bryant’s death, the comic Ari Shaffir wrote this on Twitter: “Kobe Bryant died 23 years too late today. He got away with rape because all the Hollywood liberals who attack comedy enjoy rooting for the Lakers more than they dislike rape. Big ups to the hero who forgot to gas up his chopper. I hate the Lakers. What a great day!”
